Class ItemTag

java.lang.Object
me.efekos.simpler.items.tag.ItemTag

@Deprecated public class ItemTag extends Object
Deprecated.
This class is moved into another repository, and will be removed from here soon.
Main class for the "tag" value inside an item NBT. Most of the items has their own NBT data to store data inside it. See more about item NBT data.

  • Constructor Details

    • ItemTag

      public ItemTag(Integer damage, Integer hideFlags, Display display, boolean unbreakable, Integer customModelData, EnchantmentCompound[] enchantments, Integer repairCost)
      Deprecated.
      Creates a new ItemTag that stores the values given.
      Parameters:
      damage - Indicates how much damage this item got. gets copied into the "Damage" value you see inside tool tags.
      hideFlags - Indicates a number about the "HideFlags" value. According to its number, some information about the item becomes hidden from tooltips. To be exact:
      • Adding 1 hides enchantments.
      • Adding 2 hides attributes.
      • Adding 4 hides "Unbreakable" text.
      • Adding 8 hides "Can Destroy:" part.
      • Adding 16 hides "Can be Placed On:" part.
      • Adding 32 hides various other information. Like potion effects, shield patterns, enchantments stored inside enchanting books, written book information and map ID.
      • Adding 64 hides "Dyed" text on leather armors.
      • Adding 128 hides trims.
      display - Data of the display about item. Includes name, lore and leather armor color.
      unbreakable - If true, the tooltip will show "Unbreakable" implying that this tool won't take damage when used.
      customModelData - A number indicating the custom model data of an item. Usually used by server-resource packs and map-specific resource packs for custom items.
      enchantments - List of the enchantments the tooltip should show.
      repairCost - Indicates how many level you will need to repair this tool. Goes up by 1 every time you use an anvil to repair your tool.

    • getHideFlags

      public Integer getHideFlags()
      Deprecated.
      A bit number that hides some information about the item at tooltips. Use this formula to calculate a 'HideFlags' number: (HideEnchantments) | (HideAttributeModifiers << 1) | (HideUnbreakable << 2) | (HideCanDestroy << 3) | (HideCanPlaceOn << 4) | (HideOthers << 5) | (HideDyed << 6) | (HideUpgrade << 7)
      Returns:
      "HideFlags" value.
